{"word":"δόλος","slug":"δόλος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>δόλος, ου, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ etym.\">etym.</a> uncertain, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Lat.\">Lat.</a> dolus (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ freq.\">freq.</a> used of ‘treacherous behavior’ and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ prob.\">prob.</a> borrowed <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fr.\">fr.</a> the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Gk.\">Gk.</a>)] ‘cunning that relies on deception for effectiveness’, <b><i>craftiness, deceit</i> <a href='B:470 26:4'>Mt 26:4</a>; <a href='B:480 7:22'>Mk 7:22</a>; <a href='B:480 14:1'>14:1</a>; <a href='B:500 1:47'>J 1:47</a>; <a href='B:510 13:10'>Ac 13:10</a>; <a href='B:520 1:29'>Ro 1:29</a>; <a href='B:540 12:16'>2 Cor 12:16</a>; <a href='B:590 2:3'>1 Th 2:3</a>; <a href='B:670 2:1'>1 Pt 2:1</a>, <a href='B:670 2:22'>22</a></b> (with <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ sim.\">sim.</a> blending of abstract and concrete <b>3:10</b>). <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:δολιόω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:δολόω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}